<paragraph blockId="44.[264,1323,1350,1856]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,443,1350,1376]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Identification:</emphasis>
Forewing length 15.0–18.0 mm. Male antennae are bipectinate. Forewing is dark reddish brown and concolorous with head and thorax, prothorax with a thin apical border of white. Orbicular and reniform spots are white with patches of white above both spots on costa. Antemedial and postmedial lines and area between them are slightly darker than ground color. Subterminal and terminal lines are thin and wavy. Hindwing is pale gray with a faint discal spot.
</paragraph>
